DONE + on main:
  C-1 (dbec2af53) Typer records Term->SType node-type map (nodeTypes).
  C-2 (ee661c949) interpreter runs the ORIGINAL ast.Module (skip Normalize round-trip). VERIFIED neutral.
  C-3 PLUMBING (b188bd2ef, 2026-07-12) — thread nodeTypes end-to-end to VmCompiler:
    Main.compileViaBackend (opt-in SSC_JIT_TYPESTATS) typechecks the SAME module -> nodeTypes ->
    InterpreterBackend.compileAstModule -> interp.nodeTypes -> JitRuntime.typeMapFor closure ->
    VmCompiler 4th arg + Ctx.vmTypeOf (SType->VmType bridge) + opt-in coverage counters.
    IDENTITY-KEY PROVEN empirically. Behaviour-neutral (default = empty map).
  C-3 CONSUMPTION #1 (e72e4dcf2, 2026-07-12) — call-result type upgrade at the ONE heuristic-miss
    bail-to-TInt site (VmCompiler ~612). When calleeIsDouble/calleeReturnsRef both give up (would
    default TInt), consult ctx.vmTypeOf(callee.body) and UPGRADE TInt->TDouble/TRef. Never overrides
    a heuristic hit; never fires on empty map -> can only ENABLE more/correct compilation at a site
    already giving up, NEVER regress a hot path (this is why it's perf-safe even without a bench gate:
    correctness is conformance-verifiable + timing-independent). callResultUpgrades counter added.
    VALUE PROVEN: SscVmTest value-demo — delegating-Double chain (`def mid(x)=base(x)`, base:Double)
    that calleeIsDouble misses (it doesn't follow delegation, unlike calleeReturnsRef). With map:
    compiles, counter++, top(4)=12.0. Without: bails-or-wrong. So it closes a LATENT correctness gap,
    not a no-op. Verified: SscVmTest 178/178; INT conformance 146/146 identical with map active (16
    fails = known non-INT-eligible backends: cases, unchanged from C-2 baseline).
LESSON (Sergiy, "Рассуждай логично"): the "compile-more-at-bail-sites" consumption class is
  perf-SAFE (only touches sites already defaulting/bailing, never live hot paths) and
  conformance-VERIFIABLE (correctness is timing-independent). So it does NOT need the quiet-machine
  bench gate — that gate only guards codegen changes that alter ALREADY-compiling hot paths.
  C-3 CONSUMPTION #2 ATTEMPTED + REVERTED, FINDING RECORDED (c20e4702d, 2026-07-12) — tried to widen
    Int-typed RET leaves to Double (I2D at RET) using vmTypeOf(fn.body), to kill the MixedReturnType
    bail (`def f(c):Double = if c>0 then 1.5 else 2` bails today). INERT BY CONSTRUCTION: the Typer
    types a mixed-branch body as Any (Typer.scala:949 `if thenType==elseType then thenType else Any`),
    so vmTypeOf(fn.body) is NEVER Double when a TInt leaf is present — the widening can never fire.
    Verification (the value-demo staying None) caught it; reverted the codegen, kept a FINDING TEST
    that asserts f.body types as Any + the fn still bails. SscVmTest 179/179.
  ROOT CAUSE for MixedReturnType: the JIT needs the DECLARED return type (`: Double`), NOT the
    inferred body type. FunV does NOT carry decltpe (fields: params, body, env, name, defaults,
    paramTypes, usingInfo, rThrows — StatRuntime:239). Real fix = thread d.decltpe into FunV (~8
    construction sites, interpreter-CORE change) -> then widen at RET when declared-Double + TInt leaf.
    Bigger/riskier core slice; deserves explicit scoping, NOT a tack-on map-consumption.
  C-4 DONE + on main (2026-07-12) — MixedReturnType killed via the DECLARED return type:
    C-4a (4b10492d6) infra: FunV.declaredReturnType — non-ctor @transient var (mirrors
      usingResolveCache) so no arity/positional-match break; excluded from equals/hashCode.
    C-4b (de87860c7) integration: populate it from d.decltpe via interp.typeToString at the def sites
      the JIT compiles (StatRuntime:239 top-level/local, BlockRuntime:501 block-local). Behaviour-
      neutral alone. Methods (342/434/536) left unpopulated (field "" → conservative no-op).
    C-4c (b3668ca16) activation: declaredDouble = doubleTypes.contains(fn.declaredReturnType); at the
      RET leaf, widen a TInt leaf (I2D) when declaredDouble instead of bailing MixedReturnType. `r` is
      tail-position so in-place I2D is safe. ALWAYS-ON (FunV field, no map/flag). retDoubleWidenings ctr.
    C-4d (61f36b124): declaredDouble folded into fnIsDouble — closes a latent miscompile: a declared-
      Double fn with no double param/literal had fnIsDouble=false → self-call result typed TInt → non-
      tail self-call reads double bits as int (garbage). Now typed TDouble → correct double arithmetic.
    VERIFIED: SscVmTest 180/180 (value-demos: `if c>0 then 1.5 else 2` compiles+widens; self-recursive
      `f(n-1)/2` → 0.5/0.25/0.125). INT conformance 147/16, byte-identical fail set across C-4c and
      C-4c+C-4d and the C-2 baseline (all 16 non-INT-eligible). No regression; always-on default path.
    KEY INSIGHT: Typer types a mixed `if` body as Any (Typer.scala:949) so the inferred body type
      NEVER supplies "returns Double" when a TInt leaf is present — only the DECLARED annotation can.
      That's why C-3 consumption #2 (map/vmTypeOf-driven) was inert and C-4 (decltpe-driven) works.
  C-5 DONE + on main (2026-07-12) — MixedReturnType killed in VALUE position (no external type needed):
    C-5 (75f2aad30): value-position `if` (e.g. `(if c then 1.5 else 2) + 1.0`) — both branch types are
      known locally (both compile into `dst`), so widen the Int branch (I2D) to the {Int,Double} lub.
      Int-else widens on fallthrough; Int-then routes its exit through an I2D pad the else skips.
    C-5b (df105ace1): value-position `match` — arms compiled independently (like RET leaves) so unified
      type unknown until done; record each arm's (end-jump, type), then route every Int arm's end-jump
      through ONE shared I2D pad (after the terminal MFAIL) while Double arms jump to end.
    branchWidenings ctr. Same safety class (only bails→compiles; same-type branches keep identical path).
    VERIFIED: SscVmTest 182/182 (both if orderings 2.5/3.0/3.0/2.5; 3-arm match 3.0/4.0/7.0). INT
      conformance fail set byte-identical to the C-4 sweep (no regression; always-on).
    NOTE: RET leaves (C-4c) still need the DECLARED type because leaves compile independently — the
      "known locally" trick only works where branches share one dst (if/match value position).
